theorem Topology.closure_union_interior_eq_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    (closure A ∪ interior A : Set X) = closure A := by
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · intro x hx
    cases hx with
    | inl hxCl => exact hxCl
    | inr hxInt =>
        exact (interior_subset : interior A ⊆ closure A) hxInt
  · intro x hxCl
    exact Or.inl hxCl

theorem Topology.interior_subset_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior A ⊆ closure A := by
  intro x hxInt
  -- A point in the interior of `A` certainly lies in `A`.
  have hxA : (x : X) ∈ A := interior_subset hxInt
  -- Every point of `A` is in the closure of `A`.
  exact subset_closure hxA
